Donald Sterling has lost his bid to halt the sale of his basketball team the Los Angeles Clippers.

In a preliminary ruling today in an LA court, Judge Michael Levanas ruled that his wife Shelly Sterling has full control of the family trust that owns the team - paving the way for a $2 billion sale to ex-Microsoft CEO Steve Ballmer.

In court, the judge said that 'Shelly clearly had the authoritiy to transfer the shares' of the team and dismissed the claims of her disgraced husband who has been diagnosed with Alzheimer's disease and therefore unable to manage his affairs.

