Sterling has vowed to fight the NBA until his death and is expected to continue to wage court battles to stop the sale.

The ruling in Los Angeles County Superior Court is unlikely to put an end to the bizarre saga that began in April when a recording surfaced of Sterling scolding his young girlfriend V. Stiviano for bringing black men to Clippers games.

